# Run All Tests After Changes

After making code changes, always run the full workspace test suite before finishing:

```sh
resources/scripts/run-tests-with-db.sh
```

That script reuses local MySQL or a persistent Docker test container when possible,
so repeated runs avoid the ~30–40 s cold-start cost. It also runs the Node-based
rally animation JS tests before Cargo.

## Sandbox: request full permissions for DB tests

When running `run-tests-with-db.sh` (or any DB-backed `cargo test`) via the Shell
tool, pass `required_permissions: ["all"]`. The default sandbox blocks:

- `unix:///var/run/docker.sock` (test MySQL container startup)
- connections to local MySQL at `127.0.0.1:3306`

Without this, the script may report Docker/MySQL unavailable and DB integration
tests fail with `Configuration(RelativeUrlWithoutBase)` even when MySQL is running
on the host. Re-run with full permissions before concluding the database is down.

## Manual fallback

```sh
ROBOMINER_DATABASE_URL=mysql://robominer:password@127.0.0.1:3306/RoboMiner cargo test --workspace
```

If the database is not initialized yet:

```sh
resources/scripts/init-ci-database.sh
```

## When tests cannot run

If the database or another dependency is unavailable, tell the user explicitly:
- which tests were not run
- what blocked them (e.g. MySQL not reachable, port in use)
- what was run instead, if anything

Do not silently skip tests or assume CI will catch issues without reporting the gap.
